<TITLE> Shelters open in coastal areas </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 14 (bdnews24.com)  The government has opened shelters in coastal areas prone to heavy tidal surges, the Press Information Department said Wednesday. The government pressed into service special vehicles to transport people to the shelters, and arranged dry food for them in the event of a disaster. Doctors and rescuers have been kept ready for deployment to the coastal areas, the PID said in a statement. The PID issued the statement after the weather office sounded great danger alert 10 for Mongla port and adjoining areas and great danger warning 9 for Chittagong and Cox's Bazar.
